<item>
            <title>[LU-13170] sanity-lfsck/23b fails often with ZFS</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13170</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;according to the logs this is because name lookup made by LFSCK returns an error generated by OI scrubber. i.e. in some sense LFSCK and OI scrubber collide..&lt;br/&gt;
I think lookup should initiate OI scrubber and give it a hint for FID-&amp;gt;dnode mapping, but shouldn&apos;t return an error if direntry exists.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
